===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|regretten}}, from {{der|en|fro|regreter}}, {{m|fro|regrater|t=to lament}}, from {{m|fro|re-|pos=intensive prefix}} + {{m|fro|*greter}}, {{m|fro|*grater|t=to weep}}, from {{der|en|frk|*grātan|t=to weep, mourn, lament}}; from {{der|en|gem-pro|*grētaną|t=to weep}}, and {{der|en|frk|*greutan|t=to cry, weep}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*greutaną|t=to weep, cry}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*gʰrewd-|t=to weep, be sad}}, equivalent to {{af|en|re-|greet}}. Cognate with {{cog|gmh|grāzan|t=to cry}}, {{cog|ang|grǣtan|t=to weep, greet}}, {{cog|ang|grēotan|t=to weep, lament}}, {{cog|non|gráta|t=to weep, groan}}, {{cog|got|𐌲𐍂𐌴𐍄𐌰𐌽|t=to weep}}. More at {{m|en|greet}}.

